                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-291-victim2003 t18310407-291-viclabel1547"></join>. The prisoner was in my son's service; he is an officer in the Second West India Regiment - in September last my son and the prisoner left my house to go abroad, but in a few days the ship got leaky, and returned to Margate; my son went to an hotel, the prisoner left him, and came back to my house - he continued there till the 24th of March, when I sent him away , and when he was gone I missed the robe of an African chief, which my son had brought from abroad, and made me a present of - I went to the house of 
